And he was hitting a problem,
in that post-surgery he

00:44:57.890 --> 00:45:00.320 align:middle line:84%
would give antibiotics
to someone who had had,

00:45:00.320 --> 00:45:03.230 align:middle line:84%
say, an operation in
the abdomen and they've

00:45:03.230 --> 00:45:05.510 align:middle line:84%
got a bit of pneumonia,
they were given antibiotics,

00:45:05.510 --> 00:45:08.720 align:middle line:84%
and then the patient
develops diarrhea.

00:45:08.720 --> 00:45:10.610 align:middle line:10%
And they would develop
diarrhea with what's

00:45:10.610 --> 00:45:15.620 align:middle line:10%
called pseudomembranous colitis,
so severe that in that paper,

00:45:15.620 --> 00:45:19.240 align:middle line:10%
the death rate was 74% of those
who developed pseudomembranous

00:45:19.240 --> 00:45:20.220 align:middle line:10%
colitis.

00:45:20.220 --> 00:45:21.020 align:middle line:90%
That's huge.

00:45:21.020 --> 00:45:22.530 align:middle line:90%
It's overwhelming.

00:45:22.530 --> 00:45:25.370 align:middle line:84%
And he had this idea of
doing a fecal impact.

00:45:25.370 --> 00:45:27.850 align:middle line:84%
So the first case out of
four-- and four out of four was

00:45:27.850 --> 00:45:29.210 align:middle line:90%
dramatic--

00:45:29.210 --> 00:45:31.660 align:middle line:84%
was given one enema,
a second enema.

00:45:31.660 --> 00:45:34.700 align:middle line:84%
And the patient,
as they described,

00:45:34.700 --> 00:45:38.250 align:middle line:84%
was in the terminal stages of
his terrible illness, something

00:45:38.250 --> 00:45:39.050 align:middle line:90%
like that.

00:45:39.050 --> 00:45:41.810 align:middle line:84%
Within 24 hours, the
diarrhea went away.

00:45:41.810 --> 00:45:44.720 align:middle line:84%
Another enema, and the patient
was discharged 10 days later,

00:45:44.720 --> 00:45:48.570 align:middle line:84%
having spent like 46
days in intensive care,

00:45:48.570 --> 00:45:51.500 align:middle line:90%
but under specialists, doctors.

00:45:51.500 --> 00:45:52.320 align:middle line:90%
What fixed him?

00:45:52.320 --> 00:45:53.120 align:middle line:90%
Poo.

00:45:53.120 --> 00:45:55.390 align:middle line:90%
Hasn't even gone to university.

00:45:55.390 --> 00:45:56.870 align:middle line:84%
Wasn't a specialist's
poo either.

00:45:56.870 --> 00:45:58.670 align:middle line:90%
It was a nurse's poo.

00:45:58.670 --> 00:46:00.950 align:middle line:84%
So we're more on
the cutting edge

00:46:00.950 --> 00:46:04.220 align:middle line:90%
of figuring out what works.

00:46:04.220 --> 00:46:07.150 align:middle line:84%
For example, we treated
three patients this year

00:46:07.150 --> 00:46:11.080 align:middle line:84%
with constipation,
and we were surprised

00:46:11.080 --> 00:46:12.770 align:middle line:90%
that their MS disappeared.

00:46:12.770 --> 00:46:15.800 align:middle line:84%
We write them up as three
cases where MS was reversed.

00:46:15.800 --> 00:46:18.980 align:middle line:90%
We did all the MRIs.

00:46:18.980 --> 00:46:23.120 align:middle line:84%
We had a couple of patients
with Parkinson's who

00:46:23.120 --> 00:46:25.070 align:middle line:84%
were re-examined
by the neurologist

00:46:25.070 --> 00:46:28.430 align:middle line:84%
and can't find any
Parkinson's anymore.

00:46:28.430 --> 00:46:31.910 align:middle line:84%
And I think there's going to
be a lot of changes occurring

00:46:31.910 --> 00:46:33.320 align:middle line:90%
in the way we practice medicine.

00:46:33.320 --> 00:46:37.700 align:middle line:84%
Because in the past, there was
some divided among specialties,

00:46:37.700 --> 00:46:40.580 align:middle line:84%
but now we're crossing
specialties, you know?

00:46:40.580 --> 00:46:42.920 align:middle line:84%
If you do an FMT and a
neurological condition

00:46:42.920 --> 00:46:45.860 align:middle line:84%
gets reversed, the
neurologists are

00:46:45.860 --> 00:46:47.870 align:middle line:84%
going to start practicing
fecal transplantation.

00:46:47.870 --> 00:46:48.670 align:middle line:90%
They will.

00:46:48.670 --> 00:46:51.680 align:middle line:84%
When there's a "crapsule," as
we call it, to be prescribed,

00:46:51.680 --> 00:46:53.420 align:middle line:90%
of course, they will do that.

00:46:53.420 --> 00:46:56.030 align:middle line:84%
There may be some
pure floras from which

00:46:56.030 --> 00:47:01.220 align:middle line:84%
we will extract bacteria that
may reverse, say, diabetes.

00:47:01.220 --> 00:47:03.530 align:middle line:90%
And it's very much in the cards.

00:47:03.530 --> 00:47:06.790 align:middle line:84%
There are bacteria that can
increase your metabolism

00:47:06.790 --> 00:47:09.560 align:middle line:90%
and reverse obesity.

00:47:09.560 --> 00:47:13.260 align:middle line:84%
So I've got all
hopes for components

00:47:13.260 --> 00:47:16.010 align:middle line:84%
of these untainted
gut floras, but we'd

00:47:16.010 --> 00:47:21.140 align:middle line:84%
love to have some pure, really
primordial never previously

00:47:21.140 --> 00:47:25.020 align:middle line:84%
exposed to antibiotics
gut flora donors.

00:47:25.020 --> 00:47:28.530 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, it'd be great.

00:47:28.530 --> 00:47:31.422 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:47:31.422 --> 00:47:32.870 align:middle line:90%


00:47:32.870 --> 00:47:35.530 align:middle line:84%
>> My time with the San
has been incredible,

00:47:35.530 --> 00:47:38.560 align:middle line:84%
and the week flies
by in an instant.

00:47:38.560 --> 00:47:41.740 align:middle line:84%
Tonight is the last night, and
the San put on a celebration

00:47:41.740 --> 00:47:42.880 align:middle line:90%
for us.

00:47:42.880 --> 00:47:45.760 align:middle line:84%
The fire gives them a
chance to sing and dance

00:47:45.760 --> 00:47:50.620 align:middle line:84%
and to bring good fortune
on our activities tomorrow.

00:47:50.620 --> 00:47:54.610 align:middle line:84%
The simplicity of the San
lifestyle is beautiful to see.

00:47:54.610 --> 00:47:57.850 align:middle line:84%
Their entire day is made up
of a constant interaction

00:47:57.850 --> 00:48:00.140 align:middle line:84%
with their immediate
environment.

00:48:00.140 --> 00:48:02.530 align:middle line:84%
And I know that this
relationship has a big part

00:48:02.530 --> 00:48:05.530 align:middle line:84%
to play in their apparent
health and well-being.

00:48:05.530 --> 00:48:09.040 align:middle line:84%
For a society whose
culture and even biology

00:48:09.040 --> 00:48:11.950 align:middle line:84%
may provide so many
benefits to us in the West,

00:48:11.950 --> 00:48:14.390 align:middle line:84%
it's a bittersweet feeling
having our trip come to an end

00:48:14.390 --> 00:48:15.190 align:middle line:90%
so soon.

00:48:15.190 --> 00:48:20.410 align:middle line:90%


00:48:20.410 --> 00:48:22.570 align:middle line:90%
But tonight is for having fun.

00:48:22.570 --> 00:48:25.930 align:middle line:90%


00:48:25.930 --> 00:48:28.430 align:middle line:84%
Last night, we got up to go to
the toilet a couple of times,

00:48:28.430 --> 00:48:32.870 align:middle line:84%
and there were hyena making
noises just over the bushes.

00:48:32.870 --> 00:48:36.290 align:middle line:84%
And we had that confirmed this
morning when we found tracks

00:48:36.290 --> 00:48:38.990 align:middle line:84%
around the camp, where the
hyena were actually coming

00:48:38.990 --> 00:48:41.510 align:middle line:90%
in and getting a closer look.

00:48:41.510 --> 00:48:43.640 align:middle line:84%
Today, we're going
to get, hopefully,

00:48:43.640 --> 00:48:46.280 align:middle line:84%
more familiar with the animals
because we're going hunting.

00:48:46.280 --> 00:48:48.950 align:middle line:84%
So hopefully we can actually
get something and come home.

00:48:48.950 --> 00:48:51.260 align:middle line:84%
I'm told it's a
pretty rare occasion

00:48:51.260 --> 00:48:55.506 align:middle line:84%
to actually bag an animal, but
hopefully today it happens.

00:48:55.506 --> 00:48:57.290 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:48:57.290 --> 00:49:00.320 align:middle line:84%
The San have become famous for
that hunting techniques, which

00:49:00.320 --> 00:49:02.210 align:middle line:84%
employ the use of
poisonous arrows

00:49:02.210 --> 00:49:04.690 align:middle line:90%
to bring down large game.

00:49:04.690 --> 00:49:08.318 align:middle line:84%
So this is where the poison
comes from, that we actually

00:49:08.318 --> 00:49:09.860 align:middle line:84%
lace the arrows with
that we're going

00:49:09.860 --> 00:49:11.450 align:middle line:90%
to use when we go hunting.

00:49:11.450 --> 00:49:14.300 align:middle line:84%
It comes from this worm
found in the marula tree.

00:49:14.300 --> 00:49:17.030 align:middle line:84%
And the guys are going to prep
it now and then actually put it

00:49:17.030 --> 00:49:19.580 align:middle line:90%
on arrows.

00:49:19.580 --> 00:49:22.790 align:middle line:84%
The poisonous concoction is
so dangerous it can bring down

00:49:22.790 --> 00:49:24.830 align:middle line:90%
a fully grown giraffe.

00:49:24.830 --> 00:49:27.300 align:middle line:84%
The hunters are very
careful when handling it,

00:49:27.300 --> 00:49:30.800 align:middle line:84%
ensuring they have no open cuts
through which the poison can

00:49:30.800 --> 00:49:31.760 align:middle line:90%
enter the bloodstream.

00:49:31.760 --> 00:49:35.750 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:49:35.750 --> 00:49:37.970 align:middle line:10%
In the same way
they're doing here,

00:49:37.970 --> 00:49:41.900 align:middle line:10%
in the past, the older mans,
they was come close together

00:49:41.900 --> 00:49:46.180 align:middle line:10%
like this, and they sit and
apply the poison to the arrows.

00:49:46.180 --> 00:49:49.400 align:middle line:10%
And the next man, which is
coming to them, when he come,

00:49:49.400 --> 00:49:53.180 align:middle line:10%
he make a mistake, and
the poison stab his feet.

00:49:53.180 --> 00:49:55.110 align:middle line:10%
They tried to give
him the medicines,

00:49:55.110 --> 00:49:58.220 align:middle line:10%
but it was a problem.

00:49:58.220 --> 00:50:02.616 align:middle line:10%
Just one minute,
then the persons die.

00:50:02.616 --> 00:50:04.150 align:middle line:90%
>> In one minute they died?

00:50:04.150 --> 00:50:05.240 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:50:05.240 --> 00:50:08.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Needless to say, I leave
this one to the experts.

00:50:08.660 --> 00:50:10.400 align:middle line:84%
And while the hunters
apply the poison,

00:50:10.400 --> 00:50:14.600 align:middle line:84%
I get a lesson in shooting, with
the beginner arrows, of course.

00:50:14.600 --> 00:50:16.005 align:middle line:90%
>> And you pull it.

00:50:16.005 --> 00:50:20.810 align:middle line:90%


00:50:20.810 --> 00:50:22.420 align:middle line:90%
>> OK, so like this?

00:50:22.420 --> 00:50:23.780 align:middle line:90%
>> Like that and then, yeah.

00:50:23.780 --> 00:50:24.580 align:middle line:90%
>> Like that?

00:50:24.580 --> 00:50:25.430 align:middle line:90%
>> That's good.

00:50:25.430 --> 00:50:26.570 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I think that side.

00:50:26.570 --> 00:50:33.717 align:middle line:90%


00:50:33.717 --> 00:50:36.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Woo!

00:50:36.920 --> 00:50:39.320 align:middle line:84%
The hunt is loosely
led by the eldest

00:50:39.320 --> 00:50:43.610 align:middle line:84%
of the group, a man of
almost 70 years of age.

00:50:43.610 --> 00:50:46.250 align:middle line:84%
The old man leads because
he is the teacher.

00:50:46.250 --> 00:50:48.780 align:middle line:84%
He has the most experience
and can offer wisdom

00:50:48.780 --> 00:50:49.580 align:middle line:90%
during the hunt.

00:50:49.580 --> 00:50:53.038 align:middle line:90%


00:50:53.038 --> 00:50:56.002 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:50:56.002 --> 00:51:02.940 align:middle line:90%


00:51:02.940 --> 00:51:07.590 align:middle line:84%
So we've just found some
tracks for a kudu, which

00:51:07.590 --> 00:51:09.940 align:middle line:90%
are fresh from this morning.

00:51:09.940 --> 00:51:13.546 align:middle line:84%
So I think we're going
to try and track the kudu

00:51:13.546 --> 00:51:17.360 align:middle line:90%
and follow along.

00:51:17.360 --> 00:51:21.205 align:middle line:90%
I'm quite nervous and excited.

00:51:21.205 --> 00:51:25.880 align:middle line:84%
Now, I'm really letting the
experts go ahead a little bit

00:51:25.880 --> 00:51:28.308 align:middle line:84%
because I think we're
getting closer to the animal.

00:51:28.308 --> 00:51:30.100 align:middle line:84%
It's still quite
nerve-wracking because I'm

00:51:30.100 --> 00:51:34.990 align:middle line:84%
carrying deathly poisonous
arrows, a spear with which I

00:51:34.990 --> 00:51:37.350 align:middle line:90%
don't really know what to do.

00:51:37.350 --> 00:51:39.552 align:middle line:90%
But I'm still hoping we get one.

00:51:39.552 --> 00:51:42.320 align:middle line:90%


00:51:42.320 --> 00:51:46.190 align:middle line:84%
We walk for hours following
what looked like ambiguous marks

00:51:46.190 --> 00:51:47.120 align:middle line:90%
in the earth.

00:51:47.120 --> 00:51:51.020 align:middle line:84%
However, the hunters assure me
that the kudu is not far ahead.

00:51:51.020 --> 00:51:52.160 align:middle line:90%
It's just on the move.

00:51:52.160 --> 00:51:54.800 align:middle line:90%


00:51:54.800 --> 00:52:00.410 align:middle line:84%
As we close in on the kudu, the
San become tense and serious.

00:52:00.410 --> 00:52:02.390 align:middle line:84%
They whisper
instructions to the group

00:52:02.390 --> 00:52:04.890 align:middle line:84%
and move forward towards
the sound of the kudu.

00:52:04.890 --> 00:52:22.570 align:middle line:90%


00:52:22.570 --> 00:52:24.750 align:middle line:90%
The hunters urge me onward.

00:52:24.750 --> 00:52:26.740 align:middle line:84%
And at this point,
all I can think about

00:52:26.740 --> 00:52:30.040 align:middle line:84%
is why the inexperienced
tourist with the white clothes,

00:52:30.040 --> 00:52:32.410 align:middle line:84%
holding a spear he
doesn't know how to use,

00:52:32.410 --> 00:52:34.330 align:middle line:90%
is heading up the kudu hunt.

00:52:34.330 --> 00:52:37.150 align:middle line:84%
But I'm so lost in the
moment that I move anyway.

00:52:37.150 --> 00:52:39.890 align:middle line:90%


00:52:39.890 --> 00:52:42.980 align:middle line:84%
The hunters stalk
forward, moving as close

00:52:42.980 --> 00:52:44.240 align:middle line:90%
as they can to the kudu.

00:52:44.240 --> 00:52:55.230 align:middle line:90%


00:52:55.230 --> 00:52:56.150 align:middle line:90%
They're about to fire.

00:52:56.150 --> 00:53:04.720 align:middle line:90%


00:53:04.720 --> 00:53:11.470 align:middle line:84%
The kudu escapes, and we
must walk home empty-handed.

00:53:11.470 --> 00:53:13.640 align:middle line:84%
The sourness I feel
at missing the kudu

00:53:13.640 --> 00:53:15.950 align:middle line:84%
slowly dissipates
into a realization

00:53:15.950 --> 00:53:19.460 align:middle line:84%
that the San way of life
would say to let it go.

00:53:19.460 --> 00:53:23.570 align:middle line:84%
The reality of San life is that
animal protein is a rare treat.

00:53:23.570 --> 00:53:25.730 align:middle line:84%
And thus, a diet
rich in plant foods

00:53:25.730 --> 00:53:28.770 align:middle line:84%
is what's necessary
for them to survive.

00:53:28.770 --> 00:53:31.270 align:middle line:84%
And I think there might
be a lesson in that, too.

00:53:31.270 --> 00:53:38.030 align:middle line:90%


00:53:38.030 --> 00:53:40.420 align:middle line:90%
OK, so it's the last day.

00:53:40.420 --> 00:53:43.280 align:middle line:90%
We're going to test my poo.

00:53:43.280 --> 00:53:45.632 align:middle line:90%
As you do.

00:53:45.632 --> 00:53:48.122 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:53:48.122 --> 00:53:55.600 align:middle line:90%


00:53:55.600 --> 00:53:58.480 align:middle line:84%
It's a sad goodbye, but we
must head home to Australia

00:53:58.480 --> 00:54:00.820 align:middle line:84%
to find out just
what sort of bacteria

00:54:00.820 --> 00:54:04.540 align:middle line:84%
and other microbes the San
have present in their gut.

00:54:04.540 --> 00:54:07.450 align:middle line:84%
I wonder also how my
microbiome has changed

00:54:07.450 --> 00:54:10.060 align:middle line:90%
while spending time here.

00:54:10.060 --> 00:54:13.510 align:middle line:84%
Before we leave though, there
is one last thing I have to do.

00:54:13.510 --> 00:54:17.340 align:middle line:90%


00:54:17.340 --> 00:54:19.900 align:middle line:84%
Could I order a
kudu steak, please?

00:54:19.900 --> 00:54:23.372 align:middle line:90%


00:54:23.372 --> 00:54:24.172 align:middle line:90%
>> Steak?

00:54:24.172 --> 00:54:25.730 align:middle line:90%
I know what I'm having.

00:54:25.730 --> 00:54:30.340 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, so it's not the
same as what we wanted.

00:54:30.340 --> 00:54:32.610 align:middle line:84%
However, this will have
to suffice for now.

00:54:32.610 --> 00:54:44.030 align:middle line:90%


00:54:44.030 --> 00:54:46.805 align:middle line:90%
It's as good as I expected.

00:54:46.805 --> 00:55:06.473 align:middle line:90%


00:55:06.473 --> 00:55:07.273 align:middle line:90%
Hello.

00:55:07.273 --> 00:55:08.073 align:middle line:90%
>> Hi, Kale.

00:55:08.073 --> 00:55:12.230 align:middle line:84%
>> After six weeks my microbiome
tests are ready for analysis.

00:55:12.230 --> 00:55:13.355 align:middle line:90%
You got some data for me?

00:55:13.355 --> 00:55:15.230 align:middle line:84%
>> I've got some fantastic
data to show you--

00:55:15.230 --> 00:55:15.540 align:middle line:90%
>> Lovely.

